Key Match Events: Rohit Sharma scored 92 off 41 balls, his fastest T20 fifty
Jasprit Bumrah took the wicket of Head to effectively seal the game
Post-Match Reflections: India will face England in the second semifinal in Guyana on June 27
Australia will await the result of Afghanistan vs Bangladesh match to learn its fate
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was played on the same surface where South Africa defended 163 against England
The impact of the prevailing east-to-west wind, blowing at 21 kph, became evident
Others: India's strategy of maintaining a right-left batting combination to counter Zampa paid off
Suryakumar Yadav's departure for 31 slowed the momentum
